mainmatter.p:
For a \mathcal{V}-dcpo D, a \mathcal{V}-family (B, \beta ) on D with B : \mathcal{V} is a small basis for D if the following conditions hold:
for every x : D, the family (( \sum _{b : B} \beta (b) \ll x), \beta \circ \mathsf{pr} _1 ) is directed and has supremum x;
for every x : D and b : B, the proposition \beta (b) \ll x is \mathcal{V}-small.

